import React from 'react';

export default function SVGFog({ className }) {
  return (
    <svg
      className={className}
      width="400"
      height="300"
      viewBox="0 0 400 300"
      fill="none"
      xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
      style={{ filter: 'blur(32px)' }}
    >
      <defs>
        <radialGradient id="fog-corner" cx="0%" cy="100%" r="120%" fx="0%" fy="100%">
          <stop offset="0%" stopColor="#00fff7" stopOpacity="0.55" />
          <stop offset="40%" stopColor="#00fff7" stopOpacity="0.25" />
          <stop offset="70%" stopColor="#fff" stopOpacity="0.10" />
          <stop offset="100%" stopColor="#000" stopOpacity="0" />
        </radialGradient>
        <radialGradient id="fog-corner-pink" cx="100%" cy="0%" r="120%" fx="100%" fy="0%">
          <stop offset="0%" stopColor="#ff00ea" stopOpacity="0.45" />
          <stop offset="40%" stopColor="#ff00ea" stopOpacity="0.18" />
          <stop offset="70%" stopColor="#fff" stopOpacity="0.08" />
          <stop offset="100%" stopColor="#000" stopOpacity="0" />
        </radialGradient>
      </defs>
      {/* Cyan fog for bottom left, pink for top right (use rotate-180 for top right) */}
      <rect x="0" y="0" width="400" height="300" fill="url(#fog-corner)" />
      <rect x="0" y="0" width="400" height="300" fill="url(#fog-corner-pink)" />
    </svg>
  );
}
